    "reasoning": "The module implements a finite state machine (FSM) to detect a byte in a serial communication protocol with start, data, and stop bits. The FSM starts in an idle state (IDLE) where it waits for the start bit (0). Once the start bit is detected, it transitions through 8 states to capture each data bit (LSB first), then checks the stop bit (1). The done signal is asserted when the stop bit is valid. The FSM returns to IDLE after the stop bit. Signals like state are declared as logic with localparam states. Registers for data bits are updated on clock edges. Non-blocking assignments are used in sequential blocks. Combinational logic uses always @(*). No state_t used; localparam for states. All outputs initialized with initial blocks. Proper handling of reset without using state_t parameters. Test for no syntax errors with correct logic types, ports, and structure.",
    "module": "module TopModule (input clk, input in, input reset, output logic [7:0] out_byte, output logic done);\n\nlocalparam IDLE = 0,\n          START = 1,\n          DATA0 = 2,\n          DATA1 = 3,\n          DATA2 = 4,\n          DATA3 = 5,\n          DATA4 = 6,\n          DATA5 = 7,\n          DATA6 = 8,\n          DATA7 = 9,\n          STOP = 10;\n\nreg [3:0] state;\nlogic [2:0] bit_count;\nlogic [7:0] data_reg;\nreg start_bit_detected;\n\n// Initialize signals\ninitial begin\n  state = IDLE;\n  done = 0;\n  out_byte = 8'h00;\n  bit_count = 0;\n  data_reg = 8'h00;\nend\n\n// FSM transitions\nalways @(posedge clk) begin\n  if (reset) begin\n    state <= IDLE;\n    bit_count <= 0;\n    data_reg <= 0;\n    done <= 0;\n  end else begin\n    case (state)\n      IDLE: begin\n        if (!in) begin // Start bit detected\n          state <= START;\n          start_bit_detected <= 1;\n        end\n      end\n      START: begin\n        if (bit_count == 0) begin\n          state <= DATA0;\n          bit_count <= bit_count + 1;\n        end else begin\n          bit_count <= 0;\n        end\n      end\n      DATA0: begin\n        data_reg[0] <= in;\n        state <= DATA1;\n      end\n      DATA1: begin\n        data_reg[1] <= in;\n        state <= DATA2;\n      end\n      DATA2: begin\n        data_reg[2] <= in;\n        state <= DATA3;\n      end\n      DATA3: begin\n        data_reg[3] <= in;\n        state <= DATA4;\n      end\n      DATA4: begin\n        data_reg[4] <= in;\n        state <= DATA5;\n      end\n      DATA5: begin\n        data_reg[5] <= in;\n        state <= DATA6;\n      end\n      DATA6: begin\n        data_reg[6] <= in;\n        state <= DATA7;\n      end\n      DATA7: begin\n        data_reg[7] <= in;\n        state <= STOP;\n      end\n      STOP: begin\n        if (in) begin // Valid stop bit\n          out_byte <= data_reg;\n          done <= 1;\n        end else begin\n          done <= 0;\n        end\n        state <= IDLE;\n      end\n      default: state <= IDLE;\n    endcase\n  end\nend\n\n// Combinational done logic\nalways @(*) begin\n  // Done is set in STOP state only if valid stop bit\nend\n\nendmodule"
}
